Register endpoitns in reverse so that the most-specific is first.

Micawber uses an ordered dict of regex->provider. We have logic so that
the most-recently-added regex is selected when there are multiple
matches. Because oembed.com returns endpoints in most->least specific
order, we need to reverse the endpoints in order to ensure we choose the
most-specific regex first.

Fixes #101

Allow micawber to store provider schema/config in cache.

The various bootstrap_* functions may need to make an HTTP request to
bootstrap the provider config. This patch allows the provider config
response to be stored in the cache, potentially saving an HTTP request
at startup time. This can be disabled by passing refresh=True, which
will ignore cache and refetch the provider config.

commit.message:
Remove a redundant use of contextlib.closing() decorator

Remove the unnecessary contextlib.closing() decorators from open()
calls.  The file objects returned by open() provide context manager API
themselves and closing() is only necessary for external file-like
objects that do not support it.

This should work even in Python 2.6, see:
https://docs.python.org/2.6/library/stdtypes.html#file.close

Ensure "<" and ">" in URL text are converted back to entities.

When running `findAll()` beautifulsoup may convert escaped entities back
into their actual characters, which presents an opportunity for XSS or
injection. This patch aims to resolve issue #91.
